Procedure:
Modify the SMFPRM00 Member:

In SYS1.PARMLIB(SMFPRM00), change the NOACTIVE parameter to ACTIVE.
Issue Console Command:

In the system console, issue the command:

SET SMF=00

Run the JCL to Assemble and Link-Edit the Exit: Submit the following JCL:


//   EXEC ASMACL,
//        PARM.L='NCAL,MAP,LIST,LET,RENT,REUS,RMODE(ANY),AMODE(31)'
//C.SYSLIB  DD DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.MACLIB
//          DD DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.MODGEN
//C.SYSIN   DD DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.SAMPLIB(IEEACTRT)
//L.SYSLMOD DD DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.LPALIB(IEFACTRT)
Activate the Exit After Next IPL:

Add the following entry to your PROGxx member in PARMLIB to activate the exit on the next IPL:


EXIT ADD EXITNAME(SYS.IEFACTRT) MODNAME(IEFACTRT)
To activate it without an IPL, use the following command:


SETPROG EXIT,ADD,EXITNAME=SYS.IEFACTRT,MODNAME=IEFACTRT
Error Handling:
If you encounter the following error:


CSV421I MODULE IEFACTRT WAS NOT ADDED TO EXIT SYS.IEFACTRT. 733
MODULE ALREADY EXISTS


Use this command to replace the existing module:

SETPROG EXIT,REPLACE,EXITNAME=SYS.IEFACTRT,MODNAME=IEFACTRT

You should receive this confirmation:

CSV420I MODULE IEFACTRT HAS BEEN REPLACED FOR EXIT SYS.IEFACTRT

Add the Module to the LPA:

To add the module to the LPA dynamically, issue the following command:

SETPROG LPA,ADD,MODNAME=IEFACTRT,DSNAME=SYS1.LPALIB

Expected output:

CSV551I 01.52.29 LPA ADD 742
SUCCESSFUL: 1  UNSUCCESSFUL: 0  NOT PROCESSED: 0
MODULE    RESULT
IEFACTRT  SUCCESSFUL
Verify SMF Status:

To verify the status of the SMF datasets, issue the following command:

D SMF

The expected output should be similar to this:

IEE949I 01.52.41 SMF DATA SETS 745
          NAME      VOLSER SIZE(BLKS) %FULL  STATUS
        P-SYS1.MAN1 SBSYS1      7200     1  ACTIVE
        S-SYS1.MAN2 SBSYS1      1800     0  ALTERNATE
        S-SYS1.MAN3 SBSYS1      1800     0  ALTERNATE

TO VEIFRY IS THE EXIT PGM IS ENABLED

D PROG,EXIT

SYSSTC.IEFU29     E  CSVDYLPA          E  CSVDYNEX          E  
HZSADDCHECK       I  IEASDUMP.QUERY    E  IEASDUMP.GLOBAL   E  
IEASDUMP.LOCAL    E  IEASDUMP.SERVER   E  IEASDUMP.POSTDMP  E  
IXC_ELEM_RESTART  E  IXC_WORK_RESTART  E  ISGNQXIT          E  
ISGNQXITFAST      E  ISGCNFXITSYSTEM   E  ISGCNFXITSYSPLEX  E  
